Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.18,0:00:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.77,0:00:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school student Shinichi was forced\Nto take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.69,0:00:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although smaller, my mind remains\Nthat of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.69,0:00:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is on location\Nfor a TV drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.70,0:00:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how good an actor is,\Nthere is always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:21.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century in 100 years{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.83,0:00:27.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When told to cry, I laughed instead{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:39.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century\Nin a long, long time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:45.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're leaping into a wide open world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:52.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The things I tried to\Nunderstand as a child{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:58.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}remain a mystery even as an adult{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:04.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm neither a hotshot\Nnor especially great{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.89,0:01:11.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I understand is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:16.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's neither an answer nor the truth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:23.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I have faith in is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:28.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That and nothing else {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.99,0:01:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The TV Drama Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.09,0:01:55.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Beika Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.75,0:02:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.30,0:02:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.27,0:02:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.69,0:02:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! That's it for this scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.16,0:02:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was some fine acting, Yoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filming a TV drama is interesting,\Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:37.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Popular Idol Okino Yoko (21)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:44.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Leading Man Nachi Shingo (23)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.60,0:02:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if the great leading man\NNachi Shingo would ever mess up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-chan! You must be exhausted!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.04,0:02:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.37,0:02:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an amazing performance that was!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.58,0:02:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely certain that this drama\Nwill go down as a masterpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.07,0:03:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only because you helped\Nsupervise the mystery writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.77,0:03:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have with us the\Nfamous detective who's known
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.44,0:03:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the modern-day Akechi Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}This drama's going to be a smash hit,\Nno doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.70,0:03:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose I did help a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's on top of the world now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.10,0:03:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This goes here,\Nand this goes like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way too easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.14,0:03:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be touching my things!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.03,0:03:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Nachi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.91,0:03:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't paying\Nclose enough attention to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.37,0:03:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I can forgive him\Nif it's for a cute girl like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.87,0:03:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.72,0:03:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bah. What a smooth talker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.05,0:03:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're into matchstick puzzles,\NNachi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.06,0:03:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, leading men like me\Nprefer intelligent hobbies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.03,0:03:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi-san! Good work today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:57.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuity Checker Mamegaki Taeko (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.58,0:03:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a towel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.54,0:03:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.43,0:04:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, would you have dinner\Nwith me tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.35,0:04:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She and this kid are\Ngetting hitched next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.45,0:04:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't that right, Shimazaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.66,0:04:16.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant Director Shimazaki Yuji (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.78,0:04:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.62,0:04:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.59,0:04:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.34,0:04:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They only seem like flowers\Nbefore you marry them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.64,0:04:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know it's an illusion\Nuntil it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.86,0:04:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Yuji-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.86,0:04:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always has something bad to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just what people say.\NI'm not necessarily talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.14,0:04:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my watch's alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.85,0:04:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool sound, huh? I bought it\Nlast month when I went to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.82,0:04:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess you don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.20,0:04:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you chumps later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.88,0:05:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a jerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.97,0:05:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.01,0:05:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they finished filming?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.35,0:05:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to clean everything up\Nbefore you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.20,0:05:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will, Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave it in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather is\Nthe shrine keeper here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this shrine is where I grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.73,0:05:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran-neechan...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.36,0:05:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't your friend ask you\Nto get Nachi Shingo's autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.61,0:05:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.65,0:05:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Already went to change clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.41,0:05:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.29,0:05:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec, Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.25,0:05:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.63,0:05:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Nachi-san's voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.38,0:05:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have any proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.13,0:05:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.15,0:05:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want these photos and negatives,\Nyou know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.23,0:05:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.90,0:05:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.51,0:06:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san. We'll be staying\Nat this inn tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.98,0:06:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a nice bath and a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.65,0:06:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.27,0:06:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.40,0:06:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-san and Conan-kun should come too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.29,0:06:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a crappy-looking inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.46,0:06:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A leading man such as me would\Nnever stay in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.88,0:06:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This constant talk about being\Na leading man is really annoying...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.85,0:06:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be staying at the Teitan Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Nachi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.98,0:06:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's hopeless...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.67,0:06:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink up, Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.30,0:06:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Anzai! Where you goin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.22,0:06:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera doesn't\Nkeep itself tuned up, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.44,0:06:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an unfriendly fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:06:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji-san. I need to take care\Nof something at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.12,0:07:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Hurry back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.14,0:07:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need make-up, Ran-san!\NYou're still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.31,0:07:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Shimazaki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.02,0:07:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shimazaki! Get me some\Ncigarettes while you're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.28,0:07:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ran-san! Let's go\Nto the convenience store!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it a bad idea for\Nan idol to walk outside at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.01,0:07:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody'll recognize me if I change\Nmy hairstyle and wear a hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.64,0:07:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw them changing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.69,0:07:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-san. Are you really\Nsure this is okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.74,0:07:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Anzai-san's\Ngoing out too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.97,0:07:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You worry too much, Ran-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.31,0:07:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.61,0:07:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.24,0:08:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ran-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.70,0:08:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.22,0:08:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what that was about...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.68,0:08:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looked like she had seen a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.49,0:08:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? I told you we'd be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were right! They didn't\Nrecognize you at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.13,0:08:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.47,0:08:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was an offering thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.78,0:08:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.86,0:08:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.12,0:08:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead! Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.97,0:08:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.81,0:08:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the victim's hat\Nfell off when he collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.82,0:09:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how did his vest come off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the knife they\Nused during filming!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that the killer was\Nsomeone on the filming crew!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.69,0:09:22.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinto Statue
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.36,0:09:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a dying message\Nthe victim left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shinto Statue?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a clue to who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.88,0:09:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw someone suspicious before\Nyou found the body, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.82,0:09:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But it was too dark to even\Ntell if it was a man or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.78,0:09:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that was around 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.74,0:09:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the murder\Ntook place between 10:00
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.84,0:09:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when the victim left the inn at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.80,0:09:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. This case is surprisingly simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:09:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.10,0:10:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First off, the murder weapon was\Nused during the show's filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.15,0:10:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, "Shinto Statue" clearly\Nrefers to the Shinto Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From these two facts alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the killer must be you,\NMamegaki Taeko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.71,0:10:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! Taeko would never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.55,0:10:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san. You were gone for nearly\Nan hour during the party, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.98,0:10:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I needed to get something at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.03,0:10:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our house is behind the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.99,0:10:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify that you were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.54,0:10:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather was out at the time,\Nso I was the only one there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.82,0:10:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Taeko-san came back just\Nas Anzai-san left the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.56,0:10:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After she came back, she stayed\Nin the hall the whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.61,0:10:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means she couldn't\Npossibly have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.20,0:10:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a hold of yourself, will ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any fingerprints on the murder weapon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. But it looks like\Nsomeone wiped them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.79,0:10:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.96,0:10:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer had time to wipe\Nthe fingerprints off,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.02,0:11:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why not run off with\Nthe murder weapon instead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone among you leave the inn\Nbetween 10:00 and 10:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.29,0:11:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I went to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.08,0:11:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9:45!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.71,0:11:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to look\Nat my watch just then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.06,0:11:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when did you return?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.10,0:11:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About 30 minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.98,0:11:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would be 10:15?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.56,0:11:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Nachi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.28,0:11:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you were the only one who\Ndecided to stay at the Teitan Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,instead of this inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My pride as a leading man wouldn't\Nlet me stay in such a hovel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.96,0:11:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you between\N10:00 and 10:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.97,0:11:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the hotel bar until 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.69,0:11:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty of people can vouch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.40,0:11:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking about after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.74,0:11:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.53,0:11:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.95,0:11:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was by myself, so no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.96,0:11:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer's someone\Non the filming crew...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.05,0:12:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our only clue is the phrase "Shinto Statue,"\Nwhich the victim wrote...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san is the one most closely\Nconnected to Shinto statues...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she returned to the inn\Njust as the victim was leaving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.37,0:12:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.33,0:12:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...why was she so surprised then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.22,0:12:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazaki-san went to buy\Ncigarettes at 9:45
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and returned to the inn at 10:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than enough time\Nto commit the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was 10:30 when we saw\Nthe person at the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.70,0:12:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazaki-san was back\Nat the inn by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.03,0:12:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi-san has no alibi after 10:00--\Nhe could have done it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like he was being\Nblackmailed by the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so in terms of motive,\Nhe's the most suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.05,0:12:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Nachi-san was most likely\Nthe one we saw in the shadows!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! We found these\Nin the victim's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.24,0:12:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi-san... This is you leaving\Na hotel with a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the actress Hagiyama Ritsuko!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's married!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.14,0:13:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photographic evidence\Nof your infidelity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.44,0:13:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know something, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Anzai-san trying to\Nblackmail Nachi-san earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.57,0:13:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackmail?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.00,0:13:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.05,0:13:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you, I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.05,0:13:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I killed him, then what the hell\Ndoes "Shinto Statue" mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.39,0:13:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure that's not\None of your nicknames?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.62,0:13:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.94,0:13:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No leading man like me would\Nhave a crappy nickname like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.36,0:13:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly does this\N"Shinto Statue" mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.55,0:13:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he go through the\Ntrouble of writing it down?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed right\Nin front of a Shinto statue--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.10,0:13:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all he had to do was point at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.40,0:13:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no need to write it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.63,0:14:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have any proof\Nthat I was here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.09,0:14:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This writing is weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This character isn't drawn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.05,0:14:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That lousy kid's at it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.56,0:14:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I have to--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This man was an adult, but he\Ncouldn't even write katakana right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.57,0:14:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he draw wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to write\Nthis part here all in one stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.13,0:14:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he wrote it using two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.84,0:14:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.98,0:14:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.27,0:14:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did the same with\Nthe last character too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.02,0:14:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if these incorrect strokes were\Nactually lines that were added later?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Leading man"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.59,0:14:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only leading man\Naround here is Nachi Shingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.34,0:14:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like some definitive\Nproof has shown itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.52,0:14:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit that I was supposed\Nto meet Anzai here at 10:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.52,0:14:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when I showed up,\Nhe was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this tomfoolery!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.87,0:15:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! He really\Nwas dead when I got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was about to run away, but then\NI saw "leading man" written there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I added some vertical lines like\Nin the matchstick puzzles that I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.60,0:15:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not the killer, then why\Ndid the victim write "leading man"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.69,0:15:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell if I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.06,0:15:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.54,0:15:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not normal for someone\Nto fake a dying message
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.00,0:15:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but not come up with a fake alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.71,0:15:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the real killer altered\Nthe message to say "leading man"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.19,0:15:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this be what I think it is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.78,0:15:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't have been that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.12,0:15:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no blood on this watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.14,0:15:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.97,0:15:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know the truth behind this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.81,0:15:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me! I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to how pathetic you sound,\NMr. Leading Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.61,0:16:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can give us the details\Ndown at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.60,0:16:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.10,0:16:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.\NNachi-san is not the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.04,0:16:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that the murder\Ntook place before 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.41,0:16:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.37,0:16:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw Anzai-san leave\Nthe inn around 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.68,0:16:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We even heard his watch alarm go off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.01,0:16:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. Have a look\Nat the victim's wristwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.47,0:16:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.15,0:16:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His entire left arm is covered in blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.87,0:16:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's none at all on his watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.45,0:16:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, someone removed\Nthe watch from the body
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.72,0:16:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after the victim was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone removed his watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This particular person wanted to\Nmake it look like the murder happened
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.90,0:17:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,later than it actually did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer came up with the idea\Nof taking the watch back to the inn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.78,0:17:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and setting the alarm off\Nin the victim's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it would cause problems if blood\Ndripped off it on the way back,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the killer wiped the watch clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.47,0:17:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the person\Nwe saw at the inn was--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.47,0:17:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That wasn't Anzai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.15,0:17:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who set the alarm\Noff in Anzai-san's room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,put his vest and hat on and left\Nthe inn disguised as Anzai-san himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person rushed back to the shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.19,0:17:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,put the watch back on the dead body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.82,0:17:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then dropped the hat and vest nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the killer wrote "leading man"\Nto make Nachi-san look guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.32,0:17:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer wanted\NNachi-san to look guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why not just write "Nachi"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would have been a much\Nmore effective way of fooling us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer couldn't write "Nachi."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that the victim\Nhad already written something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.09,0:17:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that identified the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.59,0:17:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that identified the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.06,0:18:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Leading man" was actually a\Nsingle word that the victim wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.07,0:18:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with extra strokes added in later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.86,0:18:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was the\Noriginal word the victim wrote?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.44,0:18:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was "Mame."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.71,0:18:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mamegaki Taeko-san.\NYou're the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.40,0:18:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! She would never!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.12,0:18:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.81,0:18:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.32,0:18:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san returned to the inn just as\Nthe person disguised as Anzai-san left!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me! I killed Anzai-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.46,0:18:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who dressed up as him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.84,0:18:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the word "Mame"\Nwasn't written there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.51,0:18:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazaki-san. You were indeed\Nthe one who dressed up as him,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.90,0:18:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you cannot possibly be the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See the huge spray of blood\Naround the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.78,0:18:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer must have been covered\Nin a lot of blood as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.62,0:18:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's not even a single\Ndrop on your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.33,0:18:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who had time\Nto change clothes and wash off the blood
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.22,0:18:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was Taeko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.99,0:19:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.23,0:19:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji-san. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.65,0:19:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.19,0:19:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as you said, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed Anzai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.42,0:19:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.87,0:19:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you didn't know Shimazaki-san\Nhad dressed up as him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.52,0:19:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I was really shocked when\NI saw Anzai-san at the front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea what was going on anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.14,0:19:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why, Taeko-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.46,0:19:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko-san. Anzai was blackmailing\Nyou too, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.97,0:19:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.22,0:19:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was in high school,\NI turned rebellious for a short time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.89,0:19:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after my parents died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.77,0:19:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped going to school and started\Nhanging out with the wrong crowd...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.66,0:19:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.12,0:19:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.62,0:19:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember when everyone\Nwas in an uproar
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after that expensive statue was stolen\Nfrom the shrine storehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.22,0:20:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.81,0:20:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.98,0:20:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After I mentioned it to Anzai,\Nhe immediately went and stole it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Sugiyama-san, who was\Nin charge of the storehouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.68,0:20:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,felt responsible for it\Nand killed himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was too scared to say anything\Nafter seeing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I quit hanging\Naround Anzai and the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.37,0:20:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I started taking school\Nseriously again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.99,0:20:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had nearly managed to suppress\Nthe memories of that detestable event!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I wanted was to marry Yuji-san\Nand start a happy family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.43,0:20:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then he showed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.43,0:20:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he tried to blackmail you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.14,0:20:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that since\NI had been an accomplice,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just as responsible\Nfor Sugiyama-san's suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.54,0:20:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me over and over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.29,0:21:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that if something wasn't done,\Nhe would ruin our marriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.55,0:21:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to pay Anzai\Nsome money here at 9:30 tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.73,0:21:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead, I brought a knife\Nand threatened Anzai back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.99,0:21:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him never to show\Nhis face around me ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.45,0:21:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got mad and rushed for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.80,0:21:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and then the knife\Njust happened to--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.18,0:21:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.03,0:21:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed strange when you left,\Nso I pretended to go buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.71,0:21:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I got to the shrine,\NAnzai was dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.38,0:21:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the word "Mame" was\Nwritten in blood next to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.38,0:21:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured you were\Nthe one who killed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I tried my hardest\Nto alter all the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.57,0:21:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wiped the fingerprints off the knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.90,0:21:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and took Anzai's watch back to the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.07,0:21:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is exactly as Mori-san deduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.49,0:22:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've just gotten rid\Nof that writing in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.55,0:22:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then I remembered how he threatened\NNachi-san earlier this evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.76,0:22:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I made "Mame" say\N"leading man" instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.60,0:22:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Yuji-san! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.48,0:22:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.67,0:22:47.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just my imagination {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.22,0:22:56.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Playing with threads around my finger\Nwhile drinking lukewarm tea{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.56,0:23:05.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's walk lightly\Nto the bossa nova rhythm{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.03,0:23:10.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The puzzle pieces are in my hands{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.12,0:23:17.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.33,0:23:27.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was in the same place last week\Nbut with different clothes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.38,0:23:34.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Step by step,\Nthere's no reason to be anxious{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.39,0:23:40.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Case by case,\NI don't care if you laugh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.31,0:23:50.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beyond the countless days,\Nshe's waiting for me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.07,0:23:55.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I gotta go my own way {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.80,0:24:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This door was locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.64,0:24:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may have killed himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.76,0:24:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. This was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.23,0:24:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the way again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.48,0:24:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at the doorway!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.16,0:24:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer is among the seven of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.54,0:24:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.97,0:24:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Luxury Liner Murders, Part 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.18,0:24:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.72,0:24:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.88,0:24:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is finally a two-parter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.76,0:24:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you identify the culprit in part one?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.18,0:24:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
